To find the principal \(P\) when simple interest \(I\), rate \(r\), and time \(t\) are known, use  
  \(I = P \times r \times t\).  
Here \(I=6596.25\), \(r=0.075\), \(t=5\).  So  
\[
P \;=\;\frac{I}{r\,t}
\;=\;\frac{6596.25}{0.075\times5}
\;=\;\frac{6596.25}{0.375}
\;=\;17\,590.
\]  
He borrowed \(\$17,590\).
